<font color="#FF0000">BEHAVIOR, NOT BACKGROUND</font><br>
<tt>Sat Apr 26  0:13:08 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
'doc' Spatz and all others,<br><br>
First, I did see on CNN a short (~3 minute) piece on the desicration of the National Cemetary on Oahu.  But I have seen nothing in my papers, or other media.<br><br>
Things have &quot;gone nuclear&quot; because people have been hurt, psychologically if in no other way.  Doc Del has suffered a direct hit where it hurts most, and where we are all vulnerable--with our own families.  Hate is hate is hate is hate, and it matters little whether there is as act of malicious violation of hallowed ground or simple words.<br><br>
Barry, I understand your re-thinking of your previous post.  But that does not excuse those prior posts.  Do you realize that in another part of this site POV still quotes you from last fall?  These words, even those we later disavow, remain and can be used (or misused) into the forseeable future.<br><br>
What I was trying to point out was that racism is so much a part of our social fabric that we need to continually evaluate what we are doing and saying.  Dismissing it as something a person has re-thought doesn't remove the sting that was originally received.<br><br>
Your being Jewish has no bearing on my observations, as they are just that, observations of behavior (in this case, your writings).  You could be a Black, Jewish person and I would have said the same thing.  Background does't matter, except to astonish me; it is the behavior that I abhore.<br><br>
I do appreciate the support that has been given to Doc Del.  He needs it right now.  'doc' Barry, I do especially thank you for your concern.<br><br>
I've got to break right now (it's dish washing time), but I will be back.
<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


